+- [RESOLVED] legal docs — Terms/Privacy regenerated in all 6 locales (en by hand, de/es/fr/hi/zh-Hans by per-locale agents, each verified by grep): former virtual-currency economy and DeviceCheck removed, Terms §10 now "Auto-Renewing Subscriptions" (yearly + 3-day trial, monthly, renewal, 24h cancel window, restore, delete-app note), Privacy §4/§6/§8/§9/§10/§11/§12 rewritten to RevenueCat-subscription reality; only "credit card" mentions remain by design. Paywall trial CTA payment line now uses localized yearly price and auto-renewal copy.
 - [RESOLVED] archive plist — cause: 1.2.1(46) was archived BEFORE the 2026-07-05 pbxproj gained the INFOPLIST_KEY_* settings and the Anky/Info.plist merge; current config verified to emit all keys (URL types, Live Activities, camera/mic/speech/photo strings, MinimumOSVersion 16.0). Regression gate added: `scripts/verify-archive-plist.sh <archive|app>` diffs the archive plist against pbxproj source truth (version/build/min-OS live-read) + required keys + extension version lockstep; proven red on the 1.2.1 archive and used on the 1.2.4 verification archive. Also: NSFaceIDUsageDescription rewritten as a purpose statement, and ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption=false added to Anky/Info.plist (export compliance).
 - [RESOLVED] identity minimum-safe set — (a) BIP39 checksum validated on import (`RecoveryPhrase(text:validatingChecksum:)`, rejects with dedicated UI error; stored phrases keep loading un-validated so pre-fix imports can't brick); (b) import stages the incoming phrase, snapshots the current phrase to `writer-base-eoa-recovery-phrase-previous-v1`, verifies every write before switching (never overwrite-in-place; `previousRecoveryPhraseText()` is the escape hatch); (c) `loadOrCreate` consults the synchronizable iCloud Keychain backup before minting a new wallet on fresh installs (all four mint paths route through one `adoptICloudBackupOrGenerate`). Tests: IdentitySafetyTests (7 passed; iCloud-adoption case skips under SwiftPM host without keychain entitlement — verify once on device).
 
